p :::s24:::Mason introduces himself as the brother of that wife -- a woman named Bertha .
p :::s25:::Mr. Mason testifies that Bertha , whom Rochester married when he was a young man in Jamaica , is still alive .
:::s26:::Rochester does not deny Mason 's claims , but he explains that Bertha has gone mad .
:::s27:::He takes the wedding party back to Thornfield , where they witness the insane Bertha Mason scurrying around on all fours and growling like an animal .
:::s28:::Rochester keeps Bertha hidden on the third story of Thornfield and pays Grace Poole to keep his wife under control .
